==English==
From Old English ''[[sceaphierde]]'', from ''[[sceap]]'' (sheep) + ''[[hierde]]'' (herder), from ''[[heord]]'' (a herd).
===Noun===
{{en-noun|shepherd|shepherds}}

# A person who [[tend]]s [[sheep]].
#(''metaphorical'') Someone who [[watch over|watches over]], [[look after|looks after]], or [[guide]]s somebody.
#*'''Quotations'''
#:The Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want; -- ''The Bible, Psalms 23:1''

